Differences between useContext and Redux
useContext

useContext is simple and lightweight.
It's states are only accessible in the component tree.
It is part of React Hooks.
Can be straightforwardly used in any React applications without any external installation.
Used in small to medium sized applications.

Redux
It is complex and heavy weighted comparatively.
It is global store for entire application.
Requires addition setup and packages. (RTK)
Used in more complex projects.
